                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17280501-34-off178 t17280501-34-crimeloc180"></join>, the Prisoner and Robert Ward came up to him, and Cobbs bid him Stand, which he not readily obeying, he cut him over the Head, and that then Ward took his Money, and between them they took his Hat and Handkerchief, and asking for his Watch, he told them he left it at a Place where he drank, and that they then mounted their Horses, and rode away: He further said, That he talking familiarly of it to Cobbs in Newgate, Cobbs confess'd it, and said Ward had cheated him, for he gave him but one Shilling of the Money.</p>
